    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-23T10:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-23T10:20:00-05:00" n="807"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d807fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SPJ1"
                            >Sturm</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>. Sent to Paris as telegram 4756 and
                        repeated to Saigon as telegram 2698.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-23T11:20:00-04:00"
                            >June 23, 1954—11:20 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 464. Limit distribution. Ref <gloss
                        target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 501.<note n="2" xml:id="d807fn2">Dated June
                        22, <ref target="#pg_1222">p. 1222</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName>‘s evasiveness re “underground
                    military talks” is contrary our understanding with him and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> that we were to be kept fully
                    informed.</p>
                <p>Suggest <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> take earliest appropriate
                    occasion remind <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> this understanding
                    and to add that our continued presence at Geneva can be useful only to the
                    degree that we are in fact kept fully informed.</p>
                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> should make similar
                    representations <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
